{"meta":{"title":"My Mechanicsville Memories","site_name":"","site_img":"https://github.com/merandagp/MyMechanicsvilleMemories/blob/main/Hincheyc1980.jpg?raw=true","subtitle":"Story of the river and its gorge","author":"Meranda Gallupe-Paton","keywords":"Gradac, Storyteller, Sourcefabric","rsspingback":"http://www.google.com/","description":"An auto-ethnographic digital history story by Meranda Gallupe-Paton about place-based memories in Mechanicsville, an Ottawa neighbourhood in the throes of gentrification. ","src":"","share":false,"facebook":false,"twitter":true,"analytics":""},"items":[{"imagebackground":{"id":"0","format":{"fullpage":true},"title":"<b>My Mechanicsville Memories</b>","subtitle":"<b style=\"\">An Auto-Ethnographic Digital History Story by Meranda Gallupe-Paton</b>","text":"<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-b2a268be-7fff-0648-7aee-ce0298f1b061\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\">This story uses text, photos, videos, and audio. To get the full immersive effect of the story, it is recommended you listen with <b>headphones</b>. Sit and</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">﻿</span><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">﻿</span><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-b2a268be-7fff-0648-7aee-ce0298f1b061\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); background-color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\"> listen for a bit before scrolling.</span></span></p>","image":{"srcmain":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/dsc_0899.jpg","srcphone":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/dsc_0899.jpg","srcmedium":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/dsc_0899.jpg"},"audio":{"mp3":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/drillingexcavatingbeeping.mp3","ogg":""},"suppress":false,"nav_title":"My Mechanicsville Memories","offset":{"left":false,"centre":false,"right":false,"custom":false,"value":"50"}}},{"textcentred":{"nav_title":"The Place","id":"1","light":"on","title":"<p><b>The Place</b></p>","files":["","",""],"subtitle":"","intro":"<p>What you just saw and heard, is similar to what you might see and hear if you visited Mechanicsville today. The handful of blocks on the North West side of Ottawa was once home to the city's railway mechanics, mill hands, and labourers, earning itself the apt name; village of mechanics.&nbsp;</p><p><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1ZgfCu_Ko2rJwbjM6-2Kj09ojY23xz_9a\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\"></iframe><br></p><p>Like any neighbourhood, Mechanicsville has seen its fair share of change throughout its many years. The Houses embraced families as work came and went. The Streets stood watch as technology changed and railway mechanics turned into auto mechanics. The Sidewalks supported the spirited steps of children as they grew into the wiser, wearier walks of adults.&nbsp;</p><p><i><br></i></p><p><i>The Mechanicsville I know, is a place that mainly exists in memory now...&nbsp;</i></p>"}},{"slideshowvertical":{"nav_title":"The House","id":"2","title":"The House","images":[{"title":"191 Hinchey Ave, c.1960","credits":"","srcphone":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/191hincheyc1960.jpg","srcmedium":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/191hincheyc1960.jpg","srcmain":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/191hincheyc1960.jpg"},{"title":"185 Hinchey Ave and 189 Hinchey Ave, 2007","credits":"","srcphone":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/189hinchey2007.jpg","srcmedium":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/189hinchey2007.jpg","srcmain":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/189hinchey2007.jpg"},{"title":"189 Hinchey Ave, 2015","credits":"","srcphone":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/189hinchey2015.jpg","srcmedium":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/189hinchey2015.jpg","srcmain":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/189hinchey2015.jpg"},{"title":"189 and 191 Hinchey Ave, October 2020","credits":"","srcphone":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/189.191hincheyoct2020.jpg","srcmedium":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/189.191hincheyoct2020.jpg","srcmain":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/189.191hincheyoct2020.jpg"}],"files":["","","","","","","","","","","",""]}},{"imagebackground":{"id":"3","format":{"fullpage":false},"suppress":false,"nav_title":"The House","title":"<p>The House&nbsp;</p>","subtitle":"<p>185, 189, 191 Hinchey Ave., October 2021</p>","text":"<p>(approx 3 mins)</p><p>Transcript:<a href=\"https://github.com/merandagp/MMMTranscripts/blob/main/TheHouse.md\" target=\"_blank\"> Link</a></p>","image":{"srcmain":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/185.189.191hinchey.jpg","srcphone":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/185.189.191hinchey.jpg","srcmedium":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/185.189.191hinchey.jpg"},"offset":{"left":false,"centre":false,"right":false,"custom":false,"value":"50"},"audio":{"mp3":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/thehouse.mp3","ogg":""}}},{"videofullpage":{"id":"4","suppress":false,"nav_title":"The Street","loop":true,"autoAdvance":false,"offset":{"left":false,"centre":false,"right":false,"custom":false,"value":"-50"},"format":{"fullpage":false},"title":"<p>The Street<br></p>","text":"<p>(approx 1.5 mins)</p><p>Transcript: <a href=\"https://github.com/merandagp/MMMTranscripts/blob/main/TheStreet.md\" target=\"_blank\">Link</a></p>","video":{"mp4":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/thestreet.mp4","webm":""},"image":{"loading":""}}},{"imagebackground":{"id":"5","format":{"fullpage":true},"suppress":false,"nav_title":"The Sidewalk","title":"<p>The Sidewalk</p>","subtitle":"<p>(approx 2 mins)</p><p>Transcript:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/merandagp/MMMTranscripts/blob/main/TheSidewalk.md\" target=\"_blank\">Link</a></p>","text":"","image":{"srcmain":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/dsc_0857.jpg","srcphone":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/dsc_0857.jpg","srcmedium":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/dsc_0857.jpg"},"offset":{"left":false,"centre":false,"right":false,"custom":false,"value":"50"},"audio":{"mp3":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/thesidewalk1.mp3","ogg":""}}},{"slideshowhorizontal":{"nav_title":"The Sidewalk Continued","id":"6","title":"The Sidewalk Continued","images":[{"title":"Sidewalk at 189 Hinchey Ave, November 2021","credits":"","srcphone":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/189sidewalk2020.jpg","srcmedium":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/189sidewalk2020.jpg","srcmain":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/189sidewalk2020.jpg"},{"title":"Hinchey Ave. Sidewalk, November 2021","credits":"","srcphone":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/dsc_0859.jpg","srcmedium":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/dsc_0859.jpg","srcmain":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/dsc_0859.jpg"}],"files":["189Sidewalk2020.jpg","","","DSC_0859.JPG","",""]}},{"textcentred":{"nav_title":"The Place Revisited","id":"7","light":"on","title":"<p>The Place (Revisited)<br></p>","files":["","",""],"subtitle":"","intro":"<p>What you just saw and heard, is similar to what you might now see and hear if you visited Mechanicsville. The handful of blocks on the North West side of Ottawa is named for its history and is home to those that live and have lived there.</p><p><br></p><p>Like any neighbourhood, Mechanicsville will see its fair share of change throughout the years. The Houses will embrace families as work comes and goes. The Streets stand watch as technology continues to evolve. The Sidewalks support the spirited steps of children as they grow into the wiser, wearier walks of adults.&nbsp;<br></p><p><br></p><p><i>The Mechanicsville I know, is a memory.&nbsp;</i></p>"}},{"textcentred":{"nav_title":"Paradata","id":"8","title":"<p>Paradata &amp; Credits</p>","files":["","","","",""],"subtitle":"","intro":"<p>Paradata explaining the process of creating this project: <a href=\"https://github.com/merandagp/HIST5706-DevLogs/blob/main/Paradata.md\" target=\"_blank\">Link</a></p><p>Music: Sleepy Frieda by&nbsp;Maarten Schellekens&nbsp;<a href=\"https://freemusicarchive.org/music/maarten-schellekens/neo-classical-works/sleepy-frieda\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"\">Link</a></p><p>Oral history interviews were conducted with: Meredith Gallupe and Dale Paton</p><p>Created for&nbsp;HIST5706: Digital History, led by Dr. Shawn Graham, Fall 2021 at Carleton University<br></p>","snippets":[{"align":"center","title":"Hinchey Ave, c.1980","src":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/hincheyc1980banner.jpg","credits":"","text":""}]}},{"imagebackground":{"id":9,"format":{"fullpage":false},"suppress":false,"nav_title":"TheSidewalk2delete","title":"","subtitle":"","text":"","image":{"srcmain":"","srcphone":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/hincheyc1980banner.jpg","srcmedium":""},"offset":{"left":false,"centre":false,"right":false,"custom":false,"value":"50"},"audio":{"mp3":"uploads/Memories_of_Mechanicsville-20211026173751200/thesidewalk2.mp3","ogg":""}}}],"nav":[{"id":0,"title":"My Mechanicsville Memories"},{"id":1,"title":"The Place"},{"id":2,"title":"The House"},{"id":3,"title":"The House"},{"id":4,"title":"The Street"},{"id":5,"title":"The Sidewalk"},{"id":6,"title":"The Sidewalk Continued"},{"id":7,"title":"The Place Revisited"},{"